====== Release Notes 5.12 ======

GridWay 5.12 is a new stable version of the fifth series of the metascheduler.

Release date: September 30th, 2012

===== Improved BES driver =====

The BES driver now includes Transport-level security, instead of Message-level
security. Also, transfers are specified in JSDL, so they do not depend on globus-url-copy.

===== Improved CREAM driver =====

Multithreading has been improved. Also, it now takes advantage of the new QueryEvent operation
in CREAM to improve job monitoring.

===== Bug fixing =====

The following bugs have been fixed:
  * Bug 126: Type and count not specified in RSL2 for wrapper-based submission
  * Bug 127: Missing special wrapper for SSH drivers
  * Bug 131: EM driver reload leaves jobs in WRAP state forever
